# Security

## Secrets

- Zero secrets in source code - no API keys, tokens, or connection strings in any file
- All secrets via environment variables; `.env*` is gitignored
- Keep a `.env.example` with placeholder values only, kept current

## AI provider keys (critical for this test)

Per `Technical-Test.md`:

- **AI is called from the backend only** - never call the AI provider from `apps/web`
- **Never expose the AI API key to the frontend** (no `NEXT_PUBLIC_` AI keys)
- **Validate the AI JSON response before saving** - reject malformed shapes
- If the AI doesn't know a price, store `null` - never invent prices

## Frontend safety

- Only `NEXT_PUBLIC_`-prefixed env vars reach the browser - nothing else
- Never `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` with user or AI content
- No `eval()`

## Backend safety (`apps/apis`)

- Validate + sanitise all input with Pydantic
- Parameterised queries / ORM only - never string-built SQL
- Never log passwords, tokens, or PII
- Handle AI and n8n webhook failures gracefully (timeouts, non-200, invalid JSON)

## Flag these if seen

Hardcoded key/token/password, AI call from frontend, unvalidated AI JSON persisted,
SQL built by string concatenation, secrets under `NEXT_PUBLIC_`.
